## ✅ Grading Criteria

**Full marks will be awarded for:**
- ✅ All 5 folders created with appropriate names
- ✅ All 25 HTML files present (5 per folder)
- ✅ Proper HTML5 structure in every file
- ✅ Unique, descriptive titles for each page
- ✅ Correct usage of all required HTML tags
- ✅ Clean, organized folder structure
- ✅ Valid HTML syntax (no errors)

## 🚫 Important Restrictions

- **NO CSS** - This assignment focuses purely on HTML structure
- **NO Styling** - Content should be presented in default browser styling
- **NO External Libraries** - Use only standard HTML5 tags
- **NO Inline Styles** - Absolutely no style attributes

## 💡 Tips for Success

1. **Plan First** - Sketch out your content before coding
2. **Be Consistent** - Use similar structure across all files
3. **Validate HTML** - Check for proper syntax and structure
4. **Meaningful Content** - Don't use "Lorem ipsum" - create real content
5. **Semantic Tags** - Use appropriate tags for their intended purpose
6. **Test Everything** - Open each file in a browser to verify

## 🔍 Quality Checklist

Before submission, ensure:
- [ ] All files have proper DOCTYPE declaration
- [ ] Every file has unique, descriptive titles
- [ ] All required HTML tags are used appropriately
- [ ] Content is meaningful and well-organized
- [ ] No CSS or styling is used anywhere
- [ ] File and folder names are professional and clear
- [ ] HTML validates without errors
- [ ] All links and references work correctly

## 🎉 Success Outcome

Upon completion, you will have:
- A comprehensive understanding of HTML structure
- Experience with file organization and project setup
- Knowledge of semantic HTML usage
- A solid foundation for future web development
- A portfolio of HTML pages demonstrating your skills

**Good luck with your "Stairs to Success" - this is your first step up! 🚀**
